title: For Sale:  PHP MV 9 Pistol (Croatia)
postcontent:
Type Double / Single Action 
Caliber(s)  9x19 
Weight unloaded 985 g 
Length 195 mm 
Barrel length 105 mm 
Magazine capacity 15 rounds

PHP (Prvi Hrvatski Pistolj - first Croatian pistol) is a somewhat strange weapon which was hastily developed in Croatia during its war for independence in early 1990s.  By design, this pistol represents a mix between Beretta 92 and Walther P38 pistols. The basic short-recoil operated action with vertically tilting locking piece is similar to both pistols, the general appearance of the open-top slide is close to the Walther but the single return spring below the barrel is apparently an Italian influence. Trigger is of traditional double action type, and the safety consists of a manual decocking lever, located on the left side of the grip frame. Magazines are double-stack and hold 15 cartridges.
Comes with Croatian military holster, (2) 15 round magazines and manual.

title: For Trade:  Raw scrap lead trade for lead cast bullets 380 38 9 40 45 12ga
postcontent:
I'm looking to work out deal to trade lead scrap for ready to load lead cast bullets. If you know anybody in auto repair/tire shop, indoor ranges with lead traps, plumbing, roofing, dental, it might be worth asking... You could get free bullets! 

Most common sources of lead are wheel weights for balancing tires. These contain contaminates such as steel/zinc weights, steel clips, composite weights, etc that need to be sorted out before casting. Depending on your preferences, I can return 20-33% of your total actual lead weight into bullets. I can adjust lead alloy to your preferences as well water quenching to harden bullets. Lubed or unlubed. Sized or unsized.

I cast:
105gr round nose Can be sized to either .356" or .358" for 380/9mm or 38/357
170gr truncated cone .401" 40 bullets
158gr swc .358" 38spl/357 mag
230gr truncated cone .452"'45 acp bullet. Can also use in 45 colt
1 oz 12 gauge slugs*

Looking for free bullets? Just ask around at your mechanics shop. For example, your average 5 gallon bucket of wheel weights will weigh 150 pounds and yield 110lbs of lead. A bucket of wheel weights will amount to ~1100 230gr 45 bullets

title: For Sale:  1900 Commercial Luger in 7.56 Para.
postcontent: This is an original DWM 1900 Luger, serial number 4160, chambered in 7.65x22mm Para, a.k.a. .30 Luger. It is an early production commercial pistol, built on the standard Old Model long frame fitted with a Type I safety lever and a narrow grip safety, a crown/B and U proofed blank chamber receiver and a crown/B and U proofed toggle train featuring a spring steel flat extractor and dished toggles with a bounce lock, its knee joint marked with a lightly struck DWM toggle logo. It is fitted with an early pattern slim sideplate and a 120mm pencil barrel wearing a fire-blued, notched front sight, and fitted with the original checkered walnut stocks with diamonds lightly compressed on the right side. The barrel is crown/B, U, and G proofed; it has an immaculate crown and a lightly matted bore with sharp lands. The action locks tight and operates properly, with full spring tension. The pistol retains about 92% of the original blue finish and 85% straw, with light high spot wear on the frame rails, holster wear on the barrel band, and modest rub marks on the front and rear grip frame. All parts appear to be original, with the breech bolt, both toggle links, the sideplate, the trigger, the grip safety, the disassembly lever, and the walnut stocks marked with the last two digits of the serial number in the hidden, commercial fashion. The correct, unnumbered magazine remains in nearly excellent condition, with a strong spring and a small chip on the walnut bottom. No import marks have been applied. This fine pistol cycles flawlessly and exhibits laser-like accuracy with Fiocchi ammo. It represents the original design of Georg Luger in its first and most painstakingly fitted and finished embodiment.
